the night I came home

248
00:13:25,538 --> 00:13:27,939
and told rosella
you had proposed.

249
00:13:27,973 --> 00:13:29,307
[ Both chuckle ]

250
00:13:29,341 --> 00:13:33,011
I thought you were
the handsomest man alive.

251
00:13:34,380 --> 00:13:36,781
I thought you...

252
00:13:36,816 --> 00:13:39,117
Were the prettiest girl.

253
00:13:39,185 --> 00:13:40,318
[ Chuckles ]

254
00:13:40,386 --> 00:13:42,287
Did you,
ludie?

255
00:13:43,989 --> 00:13:46,057
Oh, jessie mae.

256
00:13:46,125 --> 00:13:51,696
I just got to start making
some more money.

257
00:13:51,764 --> 00:13:56,234
Thinking of asking
for a raise.

258
00:13:56,302 --> 00:13:57,735
I'll walk
into Mr. Douglas' office

259
00:13:57,770 --> 00:13:59,170
first thing
in the morning.

260
00:13:59,205 --> 00:14:00,538
I'm gonna say,
"Mr. Douglas,

261
00:14:00,606 --> 00:14:03,041
"I've got to have a raise
starting as of now.

262
00:14:03,075 --> 00:14:05,176
We can't live
on what you're paying us."

263
00:14:05,244 --> 00:14:07,245
Well, I would.

264
00:14:07,313 --> 00:14:11,182
I don't understand it,
jessie mae.

265
00:14:11,250 --> 00:14:14,118
I try
not to be bitter.

266
00:14:14,186 --> 00:14:16,054
I try.
Mm-hmm.

267
00:14:16,088 --> 00:14:19,390
All I know is that a man works
eight years with the company,

268
00:14:19,425 --> 00:14:21,292
save a little money,
he gets sick

269
00:14:21,360 --> 00:14:23,361
and has to spend two years
in the bed

270
00:14:23,395 --> 00:14:25,029
watching his savings
all go

271
00:14:25,097 --> 00:14:27,465
and then start all over again
with a new company.

272
00:14:27,499 --> 00:14:30,368
Of course, the doctor said
I shouldn't worry about it,

273
00:14:30,436 --> 00:14:35,139
said I...Take things
like they come...Every day.

274
00:14:36,909 --> 00:14:39,377
What's this book?

275
00:14:39,445 --> 00:14:43,147
I bought it from a drug store
coming home from the office.

276
00:14:43,182 --> 00:14:46,718
"How to become
an executive."

277
00:14:46,752 --> 00:14:48,052
Mm.

278
00:14:48,087 --> 00:14:49,554
My boss likes me.

279
00:14:49,588 --> 00:14:52,690
Billy Davidson told me today
he was positive he did.

280
00:14:52,725 --> 00:14:54,559
Mm.

281
00:14:54,593 --> 00:14:57,662
You feeling sleepy now?
Mm-hmm. You?

282
00:14:57,696 --> 00:14:59,364
Yeah.

283
00:14:59,398 --> 00:15:01,099
I am.

284
00:15:01,133 --> 00:15:02,567
Good night.

285
00:15:02,601 --> 00:15:05,403
[<i> Soft music playing</i> ]

286
00:15:14,513 --> 00:15:17,048
[ Door creaks ]

287
00:15:21,453 --> 00:15:23,922
[<i> Music stops</i> ]

288
00:15:23,956 --> 00:15:25,657
Mama?

289
00:15:25,691 --> 00:15:27,558
Mrs. watts:
I'm all right, ludie.

290
00:15:27,593 --> 00:15:30,094
I'm just
still not sleepy.

291
00:15:31,363 --> 00:15:33,598
Good night.

292
00:15:33,632 --> 00:15:36,334
Ludie,
please, son.

293
00:15:36,402 --> 00:15:38,870
I want
to go home.

294
00:15:38,904 --> 00:15:42,473
Mama, you know
I can't make a living there.

295
00:15:42,508 --> 00:15:44,809
We have to live
in Houston.

296
00:15:44,843 --> 00:15:48,513
Ludie,
I can't stay here no longer.

297
00:15:48,547 --> 00:15:50,715
I want
to go home.

298
00:15:50,749 --> 00:15:53,785
I beg you
not to ask me that again.

299
00:15:53,852 --> 00:15:57,655
There's nothing I can do
about it.

300
00:16:03,929 --> 00:16:06,264
[ Dog barking ]

301
00:16:07,166 --> 00:16:09,634
[ Water running ]

302
00:16:09,702 --> 00:16:10,802
Ludie.

303
00:16:10,869 --> 00:16:12,537
Ludie!
[ Water shuts off ]

304
00:16:12,571 --> 00:16:14,472
It's 8:15.
Ludie: You have 'em?

305
00:16:14,540 --> 00:16:21,245
♪ Softly and tenderly,
Jesus is calling... ♪

306
00:16:21,313 --> 00:16:25,049
Too early for hymn singing!

307
00:16:25,117 --> 00:16:26,551
[ Humming ]

308
00:16:26,618 --> 00:16:29,354
Good morning,
mama.

309
00:16:29,388 --> 00:16:30,788
Morning, son.

310
00:16:30,856 --> 00:16:33,358
I'll have your coffee ready
for you in a minute.

311
00:16:33,392 --> 00:16:36,627
Why don't we have
an early supper tonight? 6:30?

312
00:16:36,729 --> 00:16:39,597
If that's all right
with you -- and mama.

313
00:16:39,665 --> 00:16:43,034
After supper, I'll take you both
to the picture show.

314
00:16:43,102 --> 00:16:44,902
[ Gasps ]
Oh, that's fine.

315
00:16:44,937 --> 00:16:47,038
What you want to see,
ludie?

316
00:16:47,072 --> 00:16:49,207
Whatever you want to see,
jessie mae.

317
00:16:49,241 --> 00:16:50,875
[ Sighs ]

318
00:16:50,943 --> 00:16:52,844
I think I'll phone the beauty
parlor for an appointment.

319
00:16:52,911 --> 00:16:55,146
Ooh,
I hope I can still get one.

320
00:16:55,180 --> 00:16:57,015
I want
to get in early.

321
00:16:57,049 --> 00:16:58,950
Mr. Douglas is usually in
by 9:00.

322
00:16:58,984 --> 00:17:00,118
[ Sighs ]

323
00:17:00,185 --> 00:17:01,386
You think
I'm doing the right thing

324
00:17:01,420 --> 00:17:03,087
asking for a raise,
do you?

325
00:17:03,155 --> 00:17:04,622
Sure.

326
00:17:04,656 --> 00:17:07,725
Hello. Rita?
It's jessie mae watts.

327
00:17:07,760 --> 00:17:11,362
Can I get an appointment
for my hair today?

328
00:17:11,397 --> 00:17:12,930
2:00?

329
00:17:13,766 --> 00:17:16,601
Nothing earlier?

330
00:17:16,635 --> 00:17:19,704
All right,
I'll see you then.

331
00:17:19,772 --> 00:17:20,972
[ Sighs ]

332
00:17:21,006 --> 00:17:23,274
Wish me luck
on my raise.

333
00:17:23,308 --> 00:17:25,143
Good luck,
ludie.

334
00:17:25,177 --> 00:17:27,979
Bye, mama.

335
00:17:28,047 --> 00:17:29,714
Bye, son!

336
00:17:29,748 --> 00:17:31,716
Now, holler if there's any mail
out there.

337
00:17:31,750 --> 00:17:34,519
No mail, boss!

338
00:17:37,056 --> 00:17:38,222
[<i> Jazz music playing</i> ]

339
00:17:38,257 --> 00:17:40,458
Can't understand
about that pension check.

340
00:17:40,492 --> 00:17:42,026
Can you?

341
00:17:42,061 --> 00:17:44,162
No, ma'am.

342
00:17:45,197 --> 00:17:47,665
Sure hope
it wasn't lost.

343
00:17:48,567 --> 00:17:50,368
You know,
you're so absent minded,

344
00:17:50,402 --> 00:17:52,870
you don't think you
put it around the room someplace

345
00:17:52,905 --> 00:17:54,705
by mistake
and forgot all about it?

346
00:17:54,740 --> 00:17:56,574
I don't believe so.

347
00:17:56,608 --> 00:18:01,212
You know, you said
you lost that check once before.

348
00:18:01,246 --> 00:18:04,615
Took us five days
to find it.

349
00:18:07,519 --> 00:18:09,654
And I come across it
under this radio.

350
00:18:09,688 --> 00:18:11,255
[<i> Music stops ]</i>

351
00:18:11,290 --> 00:18:13,157
♪ There's not a thing
like -- ♪

352
00:18:13,192 --> 00:18:14,492
You stop
that hymn-singing!

353
00:18:14,526 --> 00:18:16,961
What do you want me to do,
jump right out my skin?

354
00:18:16,995 --> 00:18:19,964
You know what hymns do
to my nerves!

355
00:18:23,969 --> 00:18:25,403
Don't pout.

356
00:18:25,437 --> 00:18:27,371
You know
I can't stand pouting.

357
00:18:27,406 --> 00:18:30,475
I didn't mean to pout,
jessie mae.

358
00:18:30,509 --> 00:18:31,742
[ Door slams ]

359
00:18:31,810 --> 00:18:34,312
Only meant
to be silent.

360
00:18:36,348 --> 00:18:38,182
[ Sighs ]

361
00:18:40,686 --> 00:18:44,822
I can't make up my mind what
movie I want to see tonight.

362
00:18:44,890 --> 00:18:47,892
Well, I guess
I'll just ask rosella.

363
00:18:47,926 --> 00:18:51,195
You know,
when I first came to Houston,

364
00:18:51,230 --> 00:18:54,699
I used to go to
three picture shows in one day.

365
00:18:54,733 --> 00:18:56,400
I'd go
to the Kirby in the morning,

366
00:18:56,468 --> 00:18:58,369
the metropolitan
in the afternoon,

367
00:18:58,437 --> 00:19:00,071
and the majestic
at night.

368
00:19:00,139 --> 00:19:01,939
I guess
I'll just call rosella,

369
00:19:02,007 --> 00:19:05,343
tell her to meet me
at the drug store for a coke.

370
00:19:05,410 --> 00:19:07,979
[ Rotary phone dialing ]

371
00:19:10,349 --> 00:19:11,749
She's not home.

372
00:19:11,783 --> 00:19:14,452
I bet she's
at the drug store right now.

373
00:19:14,486 --> 00:19:15,853
[ Wheels squeaking ]

374
00:19:15,921 --> 00:19:18,890
Would you stop that noise
for a minute?

375
00:19:18,924 --> 00:19:20,424
I'm nervous.

376
00:19:20,492 --> 00:19:22,493
[ Squeaking stops ]

377
00:19:22,528 --> 00:19:24,795
[ Squeaking resumes ]

378
00:19:37,042 --> 00:19:38,776
Ooh!

379
00:19:38,844 --> 00:19:41,245
Mother watts?

380
00:19:41,280 --> 00:19:43,681
Mother watts!
I'm all right, jessie mae.

381
00:19:43,749 --> 00:19:45,183
Is it your heart?
No.

382
00:19:45,217 --> 00:19:46,851
It's just
a sinking spell.

383
00:19:46,885 --> 00:19:48,953
[ Sighs ]
Can I get you some water?

384
00:19:49,021 --> 00:19:51,556
Yes,
thank you.

385
00:19:51,623 --> 00:19:53,591
You want me
to call the doctor?

386
00:19:53,659 --> 00:19:55,726
No, ma'am.
You want me to call ludie?

387
00:19:55,794 --> 00:19:57,261
No, ma'am!

388
00:19:59,431 --> 00:20:01,532
Here.
Thank you.

389
00:20:04,436 --> 00:20:07,138
Feeling better now?
Yes, ma'am.

390
00:20:08,307 --> 00:20:10,841
You think you ought to be
getting up so soon?

391
00:20:10,876 --> 00:20:12,310
Sure, ma'am.

392
00:20:12,344 --> 00:20:16,147
I'm -- I'm feeling
much better already.

393
00:20:16,215 --> 00:20:20,518
I'll just sit here in the chair
and rest a bit.

394
00:20:20,552 --> 00:20:22,186
All right.

395
00:20:22,221 --> 00:20:27,258
Guess I'll sit over here
and keep you company for awhile.

396
00:20:37,202 --> 00:20:38,803
How you feel now?

397
00:20:38,837 --> 00:20:41,005
Better.
Good.

398
00:20:41,073 --> 00:20:44,609
Those sinking spells always
scare the daylights out of me.

399
00:20:44,643 --> 00:20:46,744
[ Sighs ]
Well, it's your heart.

400
00:20:46,778 --> 00:20:48,779
If you don't want to take
care of it, nobody can make you.

401
00:20:48,814 --> 00:20:50,414
[ Telephone ringing ]

402
00:20:50,449 --> 00:20:52,683
[ Sighs ]

403
00:20:54,453 --> 00:20:58,189
Hello?
Oh, hello, rosella.

404
00:20:58,223 --> 00:21:01,192
You are
at the drug store?

405
00:21:01,226 --> 00:21:02,727
I'd like to,
rosella,

406
00:21:02,761 --> 00:21:04,795
but mother watts had
one of her sinking spells --

407
00:21:04,830 --> 00:21:06,831
you go on, jessie mae.
I'm gonna be all right.

408
00:21:06,865 --> 00:21:09,367
I mean, there's nothing
you can do for me.

409
00:21:09,401 --> 00:21:11,469
Are you sure?

410
00:21:11,503 --> 00:21:12,903
I'm sure.

411
00:21:12,938 --> 00:21:14,505
All right.

412
00:21:14,539 --> 00:21:17,642
Uh, rosella, mother watts says
she won't be needing me here,

413
00:21:17,709 --> 00:21:19,944
so...I guess
I will come on over.

414
00:21:19,978 --> 00:21:22,013
I'll see you
in a few minutes.

415
00:21:22,080 --> 00:21:25,683
Now, you sure
you're gonna be all right?

416
00:21:25,751 --> 00:21:27,351
Yes, ma'am.

417
00:21:27,419 --> 00:21:29,220
Then I'll
head on over.

418
00:21:29,254 --> 00:21:32,323
Now, you call me at the drug
store if you need me, you hear?

419
00:21:32,391 --> 00:21:35,126
Yes, ma'am.

420
00:22:05,424 --> 00:22:06,657
[ Door opens ]

421
00:22:06,725 --> 00:22:09,593
I forgot to take any money
along with me.

422
00:22:12,831 --> 00:22:16,033
Who are you
writing to?

423
00:22:16,101 --> 00:22:17,968
Oh.
[ Chuckles ]

424
00:22:18,036 --> 00:22:22,306
I just thought I'd drop a line
to Callie Davis,

425
00:22:22,374 --> 00:22:25,176
let her know
I'm still alive.

426
00:22:25,243 --> 00:22:27,445
Why'd you decide to do that
all of a sudden?

427
00:22:27,512 --> 00:22:28,879
No reason.

428
00:22:28,914 --> 00:22:32,416
I...The notion
just struck me.

429
00:22:32,451 --> 00:22:33,951
All right.

430
00:22:34,019 --> 00:22:36,854
But just in case you're trying
to put something over me

431
00:22:36,888 --> 00:22:38,089
with that pension check,

432
00:22:38,123 --> 00:22:40,524
I told Mr. Reynolds
at the grocery store

433
00:22:40,559 --> 00:22:43,427
never to cash anything
for you.

434
00:22:50,302 --> 00:22:53,037
[ Indistinct conversation ]

435
00:23:19,064 --> 00:23:21,966
Woman:
Morning, Mrs. watts!

436
00:23:22,000 --> 00:23:24,935
Oh.
How you doing?

437
00:23:24,970 --> 00:23:26,737
Just fine.

438
00:23:48,193 --> 00:23:50,561
[ Indistinct conversations ]

439
00:24:00,806 --> 00:24:02,706
There you are.
You change buses at Harrison.

440
00:24:02,741 --> 00:24:04,742
Yes, sir.

441
00:24:04,776 --> 00:24:06,143
[ Chuckles ]

442
00:24:06,178 --> 00:24:08,412
I'm sorry.
Excuse me.

443
00:24:08,447 --> 00:24:09,680
Man: Lady?

444
00:24:09,748 --> 00:24:10,948
Lady,
it's your turn.

445
00:24:10,982 --> 00:24:12,316
Yes, sir.
Uh, excuse me.

446
00:24:12,350 --> 00:24:14,518
I'd like a ticket
to bountiful, please.

447
00:24:14,586 --> 00:24:16,520
Where?
Bountiful.

448
00:24:16,555 --> 00:24:17,755
What's it near?

449
00:24:17,823 --> 00:24:20,524
It's between Harrison
and cotton.

450
00:24:20,559 --> 00:24:21,959
Just a minute.

451
00:24:22,027 --> 00:24:24,361
Man:<i> Dallas now boarding</i>
<i> on gate four.</i>

452
00:24:26,031 --> 00:24:30,100
Lady, I can sell you a ticket
to Harrison or to cotton,

453
00:24:30,135 --> 00:24:31,569
but there's no bountiful.

454
00:24:31,603 --> 00:24:32,736
Oh,
yes, there is.

455
00:24:32,804 --> 00:24:34,672
It's between Harrison
and cotton.

456
00:24:34,706 --> 00:24:36,240
I'm sorry, lady.
You say there is,

457
00:24:36,308 --> 00:24:38,476
but the book says there isn't,
and the book don't lie.

458
00:24:38,510 --> 00:24:39,910
But I was<i> born</i>
in bountiful.

459
00:24:39,978 --> 00:24:41,312
Make up your mind, lady.
Cotton or Harrison.

460
00:24:41,346 --> 00:24:42,713
There are
other people waiting.

461
00:24:42,747 --> 00:24:43,848
Let me see.

462
00:24:43,882 --> 00:24:45,950
How much is a ticket
to Harrison?

463
00:24:46,017 --> 00:24:47,451
$3.50.
And cotton?

464
00:24:47,519 --> 00:24:48,719
$4.20.
$4.20. Oh, yes.

465
00:24:48,787 --> 00:24:50,788
I'll take the one
to Harrison, please.

466
00:24:50,856 --> 00:24:52,723
All right.
It'll be $3.50, please.

467
00:24:52,757 --> 00:24:54,024
Yes, sir.

468
00:24:54,092 --> 00:24:56,260
Uh, can you cash
a pension check?

469
00:24:56,294 --> 00:24:58,963
See, I decided to come
at the last minute

470
00:24:59,030 --> 00:25:01,966
and didn't have time
to go to the grocery store.

471
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:03,801
I'm sorry, lady.
I can't cash any checks.

472
00:25:03,869 --> 00:25:05,803
It's perfectly good.
It's a government check.

473
00:25:05,871 --> 00:25:07,938
I'm sorry. It's against
the rules to cash checks.

474
00:25:07,973 --> 00:25:09,840
Oh.
I didn't know that.

475
00:25:09,908 --> 00:25:13,177
I understand
the rules are rules.

476
00:25:13,245 --> 00:25:14,979
How much was that,
again?

477
00:25:15,046 --> 00:25:16,113
$3.50.
Oh, yes.

478
00:25:16,181 --> 00:25:17,781
I think
I have it all here

479
00:25:17,849 --> 00:25:20,251
in nickles, dimes,
and quarters, yeah.

480
00:25:20,318 --> 00:25:22,953
One, two, three, four.
That's one.

481
00:25:23,021 --> 00:25:25,122
One, two,
three, four.

482
00:25:25,190 --> 00:25:26,457
That's two.

483
00:25:26,525 --> 00:25:28,959
One, two,
three, four.

484
00:25:29,027 --> 00:25:30,561
That's three.

485
00:25:30,595 --> 00:25:32,429
And 50 cents?

486
00:25:32,497 --> 00:25:34,665
There.

487
00:25:34,699 --> 00:25:36,400
I think
that's $3.50.

488
00:25:36,468 --> 00:25:37,968
Thank you.

489
00:25:38,003 --> 00:25:40,404
I'm sorry to have taken up
so much of your time.

490
00:25:40,472 --> 00:25:43,207
<i> Dallas now boarding</i>
<i> on gate four.</i>

491
00:25:43,241 --> 00:25:44,875
Man:
Here, lady.

492
00:25:44,943 --> 00:25:47,144
Don't forget your ticket.
Oh.

493
00:25:47,178 --> 00:25:48,879
Oh, my heavens,
yes.

494
00:25:48,947 --> 00:25:51,582
I'd forget my head
if it wasn't on my neck.

495
00:25:51,616 --> 00:25:52,950
[ Chuckles ]

496
00:25:52,984 --> 00:25:55,619
<i> Angleton now boarding</i>
<i> on gate three.</i>

497
00:25:55,654 --> 00:25:57,454
[ Indistinct conversations ]

498
00:25:57,522 --> 00:25:59,690
<i> Angleton now boarding</i>
<i> on gate three.</i>

499
00:26:05,497 --> 00:26:08,432
Excuse me.
Would you watch this suitcase?

500
00:26:08,466 --> 00:26:11,001
I'll be right back.
Yes, ma'am.

501
00:26:21,112 --> 00:26:22,880
[ Sighs ] All right.

502
00:26:22,914 --> 00:26:27,217
Kind of warm, isn't it,
when you're rushing about?

503
00:26:27,252 --> 00:26:28,752
Yes, ma'am.

504
00:26:28,787 --> 00:26:32,990
I had to get myself ready
in the biggest kind of hurry.

505
00:26:33,024 --> 00:26:34,358
Trying to get
to a town

506
00:26:34,392 --> 00:26:36,760
that nobody around here
seems to have heard of.

507
00:26:36,795 --> 00:26:38,162
What town is that?

508
00:26:38,196 --> 00:26:39,730
Bountiful.
Oh.

509
00:26:39,764 --> 00:26:41,832
Did you ever hear
of it?

510
00:26:41,866 --> 00:26:43,300
No.
You see?

511
00:26:43,335 --> 00:26:45,369
Nobody has.
[ Chuckles ]

512
00:26:45,403 --> 00:26:48,105
Not much of a town now,
I guess.

513
00:26:48,139 --> 00:26:50,441
I haven't seen it myself
in 20 years.

514
00:26:50,475 --> 00:26:53,143
It used to be quite prosperous,
you know?

515
00:26:53,178 --> 00:26:55,746
All they have left now
is a post office,

516
00:26:55,780 --> 00:26:58,115
a filling station,
and general store.

517
00:26:58,149 --> 00:27:00,584
At least that's all they had
when I left.

518
00:27:00,619 --> 00:27:02,252
Do your people
live there?

519
00:27:02,287 --> 00:27:03,787
No.

520
00:27:03,822 --> 00:27:07,458
All my people is dead except
my son and his wife, jessie mae,

521
00:27:07,492 --> 00:27:09,994
and they stay right here
in the city.

522
00:27:10,028 --> 00:27:12,930
I'm hurrying to see bountiful
before I die.

523
00:27:12,964 --> 00:27:15,132
I had a sinking spell
this morning.

524
00:27:15,166 --> 00:27:17,534
I had to climb up on the bed
and rest.

525
00:27:17,569 --> 00:27:20,204
It was my heart.
But do you have a bad heart?

526
00:27:20,238 --> 00:27:22,740
Well, it's not
what you call a good one.

527
00:27:22,807 --> 00:27:26,143
My doctor says it would last
as long as I need it

528
00:27:26,211 --> 00:27:28,445
if I could just
cut out worrying.

529
00:27:28,513 --> 00:27:33,117
But...Seems I can't
do that lately.

530
00:27:37,122 --> 00:27:38,722
Excuse me.

531
00:27:38,757 --> 00:27:41,425
Would you keep your eye
on this suitcase again for me?

532
00:27:41,459 --> 00:27:42,626
Yes, ma'am.

533
00:27:46,631 --> 00:27:48,232
Ooh!

534
00:27:48,266 --> 00:27:50,401
Say a prayer for me,
honey.

535
00:27:50,468 --> 00:27:52,202
And good luck
to you.

536
00:27:52,270 --> 00:27:53,470
Good luck to you.

537
00:27:53,538 --> 00:27:55,305
Ludie, she always tries
to go by train.

538
00:27:55,373 --> 00:27:57,975
But no, we wait in the railroad
station for five minutes.

539
00:27:58,043 --> 00:28:00,010
'Cause she's not there right
then, you drag me over here.

540
00:28:00,078 --> 00:28:01,278
Jessie mae,
you want to sit down?

541
00:28:01,346 --> 00:28:02,846
Yes, I do.

542
00:28:02,914 --> 00:28:05,182
You want to continue
to look around, go right ahead.

543
00:28:05,250 --> 00:28:08,285
<i> Now boarding for new Orleans</i>
<i> on gate nine.</i>

544
00:28:08,353 --> 00:28:10,954
[ Indistinct announcement
on p.A. ]

545
00:28:11,022 --> 00:28:12,890
<i> New Orleans on gate nine.</i>

546
00:28:16,528 --> 00:28:19,430
<i> San Antonio now boarding</i>
<i> on gate seven.</i>

547
00:28:19,464 --> 00:28:24,201
<i> Columbus, San Antonio</i>
<i> now boarding on gate seven.</i>

548
00:28:27,005 --> 00:28:28,739
I hope
you're lucky enough

549
00:28:28,807 --> 00:28:31,008
not to have to fool
with any in-laws.

550
00:28:31,042 --> 00:28:34,178
I got a mother-in-law
who's about to drive me crazy.

551
00:28:34,212 --> 00:28:38,248
She's always trying to run off
to this place called bountiful.

552
00:28:38,283 --> 00:28:39,483
[ Groans ]

553
00:28:39,517 --> 00:28:42,686
She is so stubborn,
I could ring her neck.

554
00:28:44,656 --> 00:28:48,358
Thank you.

555
00:28:48,393 --> 00:28:50,227
Her son spoils her.
That's the whole trouble.

556
00:28:50,261 --> 00:28:52,429
She's just
rotten spoiled.

557
00:28:52,464 --> 00:28:55,232
People ask me
why I don't have children.

558
00:28:55,266 --> 00:28:57,367
Why, I say, 'cause I got ludie
and mother watts.

559
00:28:57,402 --> 00:28:59,436
That's all the children
I need.

560
00:28:59,471 --> 00:29:01,505
What'd you bring me?

561
00:29:01,539 --> 00:29:04,775
[ Groans ]
I seen this one.

562
00:29:04,809 --> 00:29:06,343
You seen mama?
Jessie mae: No, you goose.

563
00:29:06,377 --> 00:29:08,245
Think I'd be sitting here
so calm if I had?

564
00:29:08,279 --> 00:29:10,714
I think we should turn this
whole thing over to the police.

565
00:29:10,749 --> 00:29:12,182
That will scare her
once and for all.

566
00:29:12,217 --> 00:29:13,650
I'm not gonna call
any police.

567
00:29:13,685 --> 00:29:14,818
Oh, you're not?
No.

568
00:29:14,853 --> 00:29:16,954
No!

569
00:29:16,988 --> 00:29:18,922
Well,
I don't care what you do.

570
00:29:18,957 --> 00:29:21,391
It's your mother.

571
00:29:21,426 --> 00:29:25,162
<i> Harrison, don tarle,</i>
<i> Victoria on gate three.</i>

572
00:29:25,196 --> 00:29:26,897
Would you like this?

573
00:29:26,931 --> 00:29:30,300
I don't read them,
and my wife has seen it.

574
00:29:30,335 --> 00:29:32,136
Thank you.

575
00:29:44,082 --> 00:29:45,649
Excuse me,
miss?

576
00:29:45,683 --> 00:29:47,985
Oh, miss.
Yes?

577
00:29:48,019 --> 00:29:50,320
Found this handkerchief there

578
00:29:50,355 --> 00:29:52,289
that belongs to,
I think, my mother.

579
00:29:52,323 --> 00:29:54,024
She has
a heart condition.

580
00:29:59,564 --> 00:30:00,764
Do you remember
having seen her?

581
00:30:00,799 --> 00:30:02,299
Well, I --

582
00:30:02,333 --> 00:30:04,701
she'd be on her way
to a town called bountiful.

583
00:30:06,471 --> 00:30:08,806
Yes,
I did see her.

584
00:30:08,840 --> 00:30:11,975
She was here talking to me, and
then she left all of a sudden.

585
00:30:12,043 --> 00:30:13,544
Thank you so much.

586
00:30:17,782 --> 00:30:20,717
Ludie.
Jessie mae, I was right.

587
00:30:20,752 --> 00:30:24,188
She was here.
That lady there says so.

588
00:30:24,222 --> 00:30:25,856
Well,
we're not gonna wait.

589
00:30:25,924 --> 00:30:27,491
The police and I
talked it over.

590
00:30:27,525 --> 00:30:29,193
You did not
really call them.

591
00:30:29,260 --> 00:30:30,327
Yes, I did.

592
00:30:30,395 --> 00:30:31,895
And they said
we should just go home

593
00:30:31,930 --> 00:30:33,597
and pay her no mind
at all.

594
00:30:38,002 --> 00:30:40,337
Ludie, I wish you would think
of me for a change.

595
00:30:40,405 --> 00:30:42,139
I am not
spending the rest of my life

596
00:30:42,207 --> 00:30:43,307
running after your mother.

597
00:30:43,341 --> 00:30:45,442
All right, jessie mae.

598
00:30:45,510 --> 00:30:47,311
<i> Victoria now boarding</i>
<i> on gate three.</i>

599
00:30:47,378 --> 00:30:48,445
Come on. Let's go.

600
00:30:48,479 --> 00:30:51,014
Come on!

601
00:30:55,920 --> 00:30:59,923
If mama ain't home in an hour,
I'm going after her.

602
00:30:59,958 --> 00:31:03,160
[ Sighs ]
Honestly.

603
00:31:03,228 --> 00:31:05,295
<i> This is your last call</i>
<i> for Victoria,</i>

604
00:31:05,363 --> 00:31:06,997
<i> now boarding at gate three.</i>

605
00:31:07,065 --> 00:31:09,967
<i> Sugarland, Harrison,</i>
<i> don tarle, Victoria,</i>

606
00:31:10,001 --> 00:31:12,803
<i> now leaving from gate three.</i>

607
00:31:29,153 --> 00:31:32,823
Mrs. watts: Wait! Wait!

608
00:31:32,857 --> 00:31:34,691
Please!

609
00:31:34,726 --> 00:31:38,295
Thank you.

610
00:31:38,329 --> 00:31:41,331
[ Breathing heavily ]

611
00:31:41,366 --> 00:31:43,200
Thank you.

612
00:31:46,671 --> 00:31:48,071
Isn't it
a small world?

613
00:31:48,139 --> 00:31:50,540
I didn't know
we'd be on the same bus.

614
00:31:50,608 --> 00:31:52,409
Where you off to,
honey?

615
00:31:52,443 --> 00:31:53,844
Harrison.
Harrison?

616
00:31:53,878 --> 00:31:55,779
Yes,
I change buses there.

617
00:31:55,813 --> 00:31:57,614
Well,
so do I go there.

618
00:31:57,649 --> 00:31:59,683
Isn't that nice?
[ Chuckles ]

619
00:31:59,751 --> 00:32:02,085
Thank you.

620
00:33:07,118 --> 00:33:09,353
The bus is nice to ride,
isn't it?

621
00:33:09,387 --> 00:33:10,587
Yes, it is.

622
00:33:13,191 --> 00:33:15,726
Excuse me
for getting personal,

623
00:33:15,760 --> 00:33:19,496
but what's a pretty girl like
you doing traveling all alone?

624
00:33:19,564 --> 00:33:22,532
My husband
was just sent overseas.

625
00:33:22,600 --> 00:33:25,168
Oh. I'm sorry
to hear that.

626
00:33:25,236 --> 00:33:28,171
I'm going to stay
with my family.

627
00:33:28,239 --> 00:33:32,075
Say the 91st psalm
over and over to yourself.

628
00:33:32,110 --> 00:33:36,546
It'll be a bower of strength
and protection for you.

629
00:33:36,614 --> 00:33:41,518
"He that dwelleth in the
secret place of the most high

630
00:33:41,586 --> 00:33:45,989
"shall abide under the shadow
of the almighty.

631
00:33:46,024 --> 00:33:49,860
I'll say of the lord,
he is my refuge."

632
00:33:49,927 --> 00:33:51,028
[ Crying ]

633
00:33:51,095 --> 00:33:52,662
Oh, I'm sorry.

634
00:33:52,697 --> 00:33:53,797
It's all right.

635
00:33:53,865 --> 00:33:55,866
I'm just lonesome
for him.

636
00:33:55,933 --> 00:33:59,603
Keep him under the lord's wing
and he'll be safe.

637
00:33:59,670 --> 00:34:01,805
Yes, ma'am. I'm sorry.

638
00:34:01,839 --> 00:34:05,342
I don't know
what gets into me.

639
00:34:05,410 --> 00:34:08,111
Nobody needs
to be ashamed of crying.

640
00:34:08,179 --> 00:34:11,982
I guess we've all dampened
our pillows at some time,

641
00:34:12,050 --> 00:34:13,950
and lord knows
I have.

642
00:34:13,985 --> 00:34:15,185
[ Sighs ]

643
00:34:15,219 --> 00:34:17,421
If only I could just learn
not to worry.

644
00:34:17,488 --> 00:34:19,823
I know.
I guess we all ask that.

645
00:34:19,857 --> 00:34:22,626
Jessie mae, my daughter-in-law,
she don't worry.

646
00:34:22,660 --> 00:34:24,127
"What for?" She says.

647
00:34:24,162 --> 00:34:26,063
Well,
like I tell her,

648
00:34:26,130 --> 00:34:29,433
it's a fine attitude
if you can cultivate it.

649
00:34:29,467 --> 00:34:32,102
Trouble is,
I can't do it no more.

650
00:34:32,170 --> 00:34:33,336
It is hard.

651
00:34:33,371 --> 00:34:36,039
I didn't
used to worry.

652
00:34:36,074 --> 00:34:39,009
I was so carefree
as a girl.

653
00:34:39,043 --> 00:34:40,510
[ Chuckles ]

654
00:34:40,578 --> 00:34:42,379
I had lots to worry me,
too.

655
00:34:42,447 --> 00:34:45,582
Everybody in bountiful
was so poor.

656
00:34:45,616 --> 00:34:47,284
But we got along.

657
00:34:47,318 --> 00:34:52,389
I said to my papa once after
our third crop failure in a row,

658
00:34:52,423 --> 00:34:55,759
"whoever gave this place
the name of bountiful?"

659
00:34:55,793 --> 00:34:57,360
His papa did,
he said,

660
00:34:57,395 --> 00:35:00,664
because in those days,
it was a land of plenty.

661
00:35:00,698 --> 00:35:03,733
All you had to do
is drop seeds in the ground

662
00:35:03,768 --> 00:35:06,203
and crops
would just spring up --

663
00:35:06,237 --> 00:35:09,673
cotton, corn,
and sugar cane.

664
00:35:09,707 --> 00:35:14,945
I still think it's
the prettiest place I know of.

665
00:35:14,979 --> 00:35:17,214
Jessie mae
says it's the ugliest.

666
00:35:17,248 --> 00:35:20,250
She's just says that,
I know, to make me mad.

667
00:35:20,284 --> 00:35:24,054
And then Sonny --
that's my boy, ludie --

668
00:35:24,088 --> 00:35:28,291
he says
not to answer her back

669
00:35:28,326 --> 00:35:30,193
'cause it only
causes argument

670
00:35:30,261 --> 00:35:33,063
and nobody ever won an argument
with jessie mae.

671
00:35:33,097 --> 00:35:36,032
And I guess that's right.
[ Chuckles ]

672
00:35:36,067 --> 00:35:38,168
Mrs. watts?

673
00:35:38,236 --> 00:35:39,302
Yes?

674
00:35:39,370 --> 00:35:41,171
I think
I ought to tell you this.

675
00:35:41,205 --> 00:35:43,640
I don't want you to think I'm
interfering in your business,

676
00:35:43,674 --> 00:35:46,343
but your son and daughter-in-law
came in after you left.

677
00:35:46,410 --> 00:35:47,744
No, I know.
I saw them coming.

678
00:35:47,778 --> 00:35:49,312
That's why I ran out
so fast.

679
00:35:49,347 --> 00:35:50,580
[ Chuckles ]

680
00:35:50,648 --> 00:35:53,016
Your son
seemed very concerned.

681
00:35:53,084 --> 00:35:54,217
Bless his heart.

682
00:35:54,285 --> 00:35:56,953
He found a handkerchief
you had left.

683
00:35:56,988 --> 00:35:59,089
[ Gasps ]
Mercy, that's right.

684
00:35:59,157 --> 00:36:00,991
He asked
if I seen you.

685
00:36:01,058 --> 00:36:03,193
I felt like
I<i> had</i> to say yes.

686
00:36:03,227 --> 00:36:04,961
I wouldn't have said anything
if he hadn't asked.

687
00:36:04,996 --> 00:36:07,631
Oh.
That's all right.

688
00:36:07,665 --> 00:36:12,702
I would have done the same thing
in your place.

689
00:36:14,071 --> 00:36:16,406
Did you talk
to jessie mae?

690
00:36:16,474 --> 00:36:18,875
Yes.
Isn't she a sight?

691
00:36:18,910 --> 00:36:20,343
[ Both chuckle ]

692
00:36:26,551 --> 00:36:32,355
I think ludie knows how I feel
about getting back to bountiful.

693
00:36:32,423 --> 00:36:35,292
Once when I was talking
about something

694
00:36:35,326 --> 00:36:39,262
we did back there in the old
days, he just bust out crying.

695
00:36:39,297 --> 00:36:44,134
He was so overcome, he jumped up
and ran out the room.

696
00:36:58,616 --> 00:37:01,117
[ Humming ]

697
00:37:01,152 --> 00:37:02,786
That's a pretty hymn.

698
00:37:02,820 --> 00:37:04,721
What's the name
of it?

699
00:37:04,755 --> 00:37:07,857
"There's not a friend
like the lowly Jesus."

700
00:37:07,925 --> 00:37:09,025
You like hymns?

701
00:37:09,093 --> 00:37:10,794
Yes, I do.
So do I.

702
00:37:10,828 --> 00:37:13,730
I bet I sing it
a hundred times a day

703
00:37:13,798 --> 00:37:15,966
when jessie mae
ain't home.

704
00:37:16,033 --> 00:37:18,501
Hymns make
jessie mae nervous.

705
00:37:18,569 --> 00:37:21,037
So many people
are nervous today.

706
00:37:21,072 --> 00:37:23,607
Ludie wasn't nervous
back in bountiful.

707
00:37:23,641 --> 00:37:25,175
Neither was I.

708
00:37:25,209 --> 00:37:29,145
Breeze from the Gulf
would always quiet your nerves.

709
00:37:29,213 --> 00:37:32,015
You can sit
on your front gallery

710
00:37:32,083 --> 00:37:35,085
and smell the ocean
blowing in around you.

711
00:37:35,119 --> 00:37:36,653
[ Chuckles ]

712
00:37:36,721 --> 00:37:41,091
Callie says I could always
come back and visit with her.

713
00:37:41,125 --> 00:37:42,993
She meant that,
too.

714
00:37:43,060 --> 00:37:46,263
That's who I'm gonna stay with,
Callie Davis.

715
00:37:46,297 --> 00:37:50,000
I get a card from her
every Christmas.

716
00:37:50,034 --> 00:37:54,738
I wrote her last week,
and I told her to expect me.

717
00:37:54,772 --> 00:38:00,610
I got to get back and smell that
salt air and work that dirt.

718
00:38:06,550 --> 00:38:08,885
Where do you go
from Harrison?

719
00:38:08,919 --> 00:38:10,186
Old Gulf.

720
00:38:10,221 --> 00:38:12,656
My family just moved there
from Louisiana.

721
00:38:12,690 --> 00:38:13,957
Hmm.

722
00:38:13,991 --> 00:38:15,859
I'll stay there
until my husband comes home.

723
00:38:15,893 --> 00:38:17,160
That's nice.

724
00:38:17,228 --> 00:38:19,462
It's gonna be funny
living at home again.

725
00:38:19,497 --> 00:38:21,531
How long
have you been married?

726
00:38:21,565 --> 00:38:22,666
A year.

727
00:38:22,700 --> 00:38:24,434
My husband was anxious
for me to go.

728
00:38:24,468 --> 00:38:27,070
He said he'd worry
about me being alone.

729
00:38:27,104 --> 00:38:28,238
I'm the only child.

730
00:38:28,272 --> 00:38:29,572
My parents and I
are very close.

731
00:38:29,607 --> 00:38:31,207
That's nice.

732
00:38:31,275 --> 00:38:34,311
I so hoped my mother and daddy
would like my husband

733
00:38:34,378 --> 00:38:35,679
and he'd like them.

734
00:38:35,713 --> 00:38:37,013
I needn't have worried.

735
00:38:37,048 --> 00:38:39,683
They liked each other
from the very first.

736
00:38:39,717 --> 00:38:40,884
[ Chuckles ]

737
00:38:40,918 --> 00:38:42,819
Mother and daddy said
they feel like

738
00:38:42,853 --> 00:38:46,656
they have<i> two</i> children now --
a son<i> and</i> a daughter.

739
00:38:46,691 --> 00:38:48,425
Isn't that nice?

740
00:38:48,492 --> 00:38:53,163
I've heard people say
that when your son marries,

741
00:38:53,197 --> 00:38:54,431
you lose a son,

742
00:38:54,498 --> 00:38:57,233
but when your daughter marries,
you get a son.

743
00:38:57,268 --> 00:38:59,069
What's your husband's name?

744
00:38:59,103 --> 00:39:00,837
Robert.

745
00:39:00,905 --> 00:39:02,505
That's a nice name.

746
00:39:02,573 --> 00:39:03,907
I think so.

747
00:39:03,941 --> 00:39:07,177
But I guess any name he had
I'd think was nice.

748
00:39:07,244 --> 00:39:09,646
I love my husband
very much.

749
00:39:09,714 --> 00:39:13,950
Lots of girls I know
think I'm silly about him,

