Well,
that's good.

1002
00:53:07,217 --> 00:53:11,754
I got one boy that drinks,
one boy that doesn't.

1003
00:53:11,821 --> 00:53:13,122
I can't understand it.

1004
00:53:13,156 --> 00:53:14,723
I raised them
the same way.

1005
00:53:14,758 --> 00:53:15,824
I know.

1006
00:53:15,859 --> 00:53:19,395
I've knew
other cases like that --

1007
00:53:19,462 --> 00:53:22,932
one drinks,
the other one doesn't.

1008
00:53:22,999 --> 00:53:25,467
I don't know why.

1009
00:53:25,535 --> 00:53:29,071
Friend of mine's
got a girl that drinks.

1010
00:53:29,139 --> 00:53:32,841
I think that's the saddest thing
in the world.

1011
00:53:32,909 --> 00:53:34,910
Isn't it?

1012
00:53:34,978 --> 00:53:38,714
Well,
good night.

1013
00:53:38,782 --> 00:53:41,684
Good night.

1014
00:53:46,790 --> 00:53:49,024
Good night.

1015
00:53:49,059 --> 00:53:51,227
Good night.

1016
00:53:58,335 --> 00:54:00,636
[ Birds chirping, dog barking ]

1017
00:54:16,319 --> 00:54:18,454
Roy?

1018
00:54:20,857 --> 00:54:22,324
Come on, Roy.
Wake up.

1019
00:54:22,359 --> 00:54:23,759
Oh.
Hello, sheriff.

1020
00:54:23,793 --> 00:54:26,161
How long
has that old lady been here?

1021
00:54:26,196 --> 00:54:31,500
Oh...
About six hours.

1022
00:54:31,534 --> 00:54:32,768
She come off the bus
from Houston?

1023
00:54:32,802 --> 00:54:35,170
Yes, sir.
I know her name.

1024
00:54:35,205 --> 00:54:36,305
It's watts.

1025
00:54:36,373 --> 00:54:38,173
She left a purse
on the bus.

1026
00:54:38,241 --> 00:54:40,476
I had to call up to don tarle
about it.

1027
00:54:40,543 --> 00:54:41,910
Do you have her purse?

1028
00:54:41,945 --> 00:54:43,379
Yes, sir. Just came.

1029
00:54:51,388 --> 00:54:53,522
Yeah,
she's the one, all right.

1030
00:54:53,556 --> 00:54:55,324
Got a call
from the Houston police.

1031
00:54:55,358 --> 00:54:57,693
They want me to hold her
till her son comes for her.

1032
00:54:57,727 --> 00:54:59,662
She says
she used to live in bountiful.

1033
00:54:59,696 --> 00:55:03,198
Her son claims
that she's not responsible.

1034
00:55:03,233 --> 00:55:05,301
She act crazy
to you?

1035
00:55:05,335 --> 00:55:08,437
Not that I noticed.
Is she crazy?

1036
00:55:08,471 --> 00:55:09,805
Well,
they say so.

1037
00:55:16,513 --> 00:55:18,647
Oh,
she's sleeping so sound.

1038
00:55:18,682 --> 00:55:21,116
[ Clicks tongue ]
I tell you what.

1039
00:55:21,151 --> 00:55:24,253
I'll go down, call Houston,
tell them she's here.

1040
00:55:24,287 --> 00:55:26,055
Her son's coming
in his car.

1041
00:55:26,089 --> 00:55:27,589
He'll be here
about 7:30.

1042
00:55:27,624 --> 00:55:29,625
I'll be back
in about 10 minutes.

1043
00:55:29,659 --> 00:55:31,794
If she gives you any trouble,
just call me.

1044
00:55:31,828 --> 00:55:33,062
Roy: Yes, sir.

1045
00:55:47,744 --> 00:55:50,279
Good morning.
Good morning.

1046
00:55:50,347 --> 00:55:52,815
Did my purse arrive?

1047
00:55:52,849 --> 00:55:54,683
Yes, ma'am.

1048
00:55:56,353 --> 00:55:58,687
Thank you so much.
You're welcome.

1049
00:55:58,722 --> 00:56:01,290
I wonder if you could cash
a check for me.

1050
00:56:01,358 --> 00:56:02,591
Why?

1051
00:56:02,625 --> 00:56:05,027
I need money to get me started
in bountiful.

1052
00:56:05,095 --> 00:56:06,895
I'm sorry, lady, but you're not
going to bountiful.

1053
00:56:06,963 --> 00:56:08,364
Oh, yes, I am.
You see, I --

1054
00:56:08,431 --> 00:56:09,732
I'm sorry,
lady.

1055
00:56:09,799 --> 00:56:11,266
I got to hold you here
for the sheriff.

1056
00:56:11,301 --> 00:56:12,968
The sheriff?
Yes, ma'am.

1057
00:56:13,036 --> 00:56:14,703
You're joking
with me.

1058
00:56:14,738 --> 00:56:16,605
Please don't joke
with me.

1059
00:56:16,639 --> 00:56:18,173
I've come too far.

1060
00:56:18,241 --> 00:56:21,276
I got to keep you here till
your son arrives in his car.

1061
00:56:21,311 --> 00:56:24,380
My son hasn't got a car,
so I don't believe you.

1062
00:56:24,447 --> 00:56:26,482
The sheriff will be here
in a minute.

1063
00:56:26,549 --> 00:56:28,684
You can ask him yourself.

1064
00:56:28,752 --> 00:56:30,686
All right.

1065
00:56:30,754 --> 00:56:33,222
But I'm going.
Do you understand that?

1066
00:56:33,289 --> 00:56:36,792
This is a free country,
and I'll tell him that.

1067
00:56:36,826 --> 00:56:39,728
No sheriff,
no king, no prison

1068
00:56:39,796 --> 00:56:41,897
will keep me
from going back to bountiful.

1069
00:56:41,965 --> 00:56:43,399
All right!

1070
00:56:43,433 --> 00:56:45,334
You can tell him yourself.

1071
00:56:45,402 --> 00:56:47,603
What time
is my son expected?

1072
00:56:47,670 --> 00:56:52,174
The sheriff said
around 7:30.

1073
00:56:52,242 --> 00:56:56,678
Where can I
get me a driver?

1074
00:56:56,746 --> 00:56:57,880
Ma'am.

1075
00:56:57,947 --> 00:57:00,215
If you
can get me a driver,

1076
00:57:00,283 --> 00:57:04,119
I can make it to bountiful
and back way before 7:30.

1077
00:57:04,154 --> 00:57:05,521
Look, lady --

1078
00:57:05,555 --> 00:57:07,723
that's all I want.
That's all I ask.

1079
00:57:07,757 --> 00:57:09,224
Just to see it,

1080
00:57:09,292 --> 00:57:12,661
to stand on the porch
of my own house once more.

1081
00:57:12,695 --> 00:57:13,962
Lady --

1082
00:57:14,030 --> 00:57:16,265
last night,
I thought I had to stay.

1083
00:57:16,332 --> 00:57:19,368
I thought I would die
if I couldn't stay.

1084
00:57:19,402 --> 00:57:21,837
But I'll settle
for less now.

1085
00:57:21,905 --> 00:57:24,406
An hour, half hour,
15 minutes.

1086
00:57:24,474 --> 00:57:26,809
Look, look, lady,
it ain't up to me.

1087
00:57:26,843 --> 00:57:28,577
I told you -- the sheriff.

1088
00:57:28,611 --> 00:57:29,745
Then get me the sheriff.

1089
00:57:29,779 --> 00:57:31,146
Go get me
the sheriff.

1090
00:57:31,214 --> 00:57:33,482
The time is going, sir.
The time is going.

1091
00:57:33,550 --> 00:57:35,250
The time is --
Mrs. watts.

1092
00:57:36,386 --> 00:57:38,921
Yes, sir?

1093
00:57:38,955 --> 00:57:41,757
Are you the sheriff?

1094
00:57:41,825 --> 00:57:43,559
Yes, ma'am.

1095
00:57:43,593 --> 00:57:46,829
I understand
my son will be here at 7:30

1096
00:57:46,863 --> 00:57:49,364
to take me back
to Houston.

1097
00:57:49,399 --> 00:57:50,566
Yes, ma'am.

1098
00:57:52,135 --> 00:57:54,069
Please listen to me,
sir.

1099
00:57:54,103 --> 00:57:57,372
I've waited a long time
just to get to bountiful.

1100
00:57:57,407 --> 00:57:59,942
And I made one promise
to myself,

1101
00:57:59,976 --> 00:58:03,078
and that is to see my home again
before I die.

1102
00:58:03,112 --> 00:58:04,880
Lady, I don't know anything
about that.

1103
00:58:04,914 --> 00:58:06,548
I'm not asking
that I not go back.

1104
00:58:06,583 --> 00:58:07,749
I'm willing
to go back.

1105
00:58:07,784 --> 00:58:12,221
Only let me travel
these 12 Miles first.

1106
00:58:12,255 --> 00:58:13,655
I got money.

1107
00:58:13,690 --> 00:58:15,557
I can pay.

1108
00:58:16,526 --> 00:58:19,194
Ma'am, I think that's between
you an your son.

1109
00:58:19,229 --> 00:58:21,730
Ludie? He has to do what
jessie mae tells him to do.

1110
00:58:21,764 --> 00:58:23,198
I know
why she wants me back.

1111
00:58:23,233 --> 00:58:24,800
It's for
my government check.

1112
00:58:24,834 --> 00:58:26,101
I don't know anything
about that, ma'am.

1113
00:58:26,135 --> 00:58:27,503
Won't you let me go?

1114
00:58:27,537 --> 00:58:29,771
No. Not unless
your son takes you.

1115
00:58:32,675 --> 00:58:35,577
All right.

1116
00:58:35,612 --> 00:58:38,914
Then I've lost.

1117
00:58:41,184 --> 00:58:44,486
I've come all this way
only to lose.

1118
00:58:47,423 --> 00:58:53,228
I kept thinking back there, day
and night in those two rooms.

1119
00:58:53,263 --> 00:58:55,264
I kept thinking.

1120
00:58:55,331 --> 00:59:00,035
And it may mean
nothing at all to you,

1121
00:59:00,103 --> 00:59:02,371
but I kept thinking

1122
00:59:02,438 --> 00:59:09,344
if I could just set foot there
for a minute, even a second,

1123
00:59:09,412 --> 00:59:14,316
I might get
some understanding of why --

1124
00:59:14,350 --> 00:59:19,922
why my life has grown so empty
and meaningless

1125
00:59:19,956 --> 00:59:26,762
and why I've turned into a
hateful, quarrelsome old woman.

1126
00:59:29,399 --> 00:59:34,202
And before I leave this earth,
I'd like to recover

1127
00:59:34,237 --> 00:59:39,007
some of the dignity
and the peace I used to know.

1128
00:59:40,843 --> 00:59:45,314
I'm going to die,
and jessie mae knows that.

1129
00:59:45,348 --> 00:59:47,516
And she's willful.

1130
00:59:47,584 --> 00:59:53,188
And it's her will that I die
in those two rooms.

1131
00:59:53,222 --> 00:59:57,192
Well,
she won't have her way.

1132
00:59:57,293 --> 01:00:02,531
Because it's<i> my</i> will
to die in bountiful.

1133
01:00:02,565 --> 01:00:04,833
I want to go home.

1134
01:00:04,901 --> 01:00:06,668
B-b-b-but, Mrs. watts --
I want to go home.

1135
01:00:06,736 --> 01:00:08,270
Roy, Roy,
hurry up now.

1136
01:00:08,304 --> 01:00:10,238
Call the doctor.
Roy: Yes, sir.

1137
01:00:10,273 --> 01:00:11,573
No doctor!
No doctor!

1138
01:00:11,641 --> 01:00:13,041
Sit, sit,
sit, sit.

1139
01:00:13,076 --> 01:00:15,010
Bountiful!
Bountiful! Bountiful!

1140
01:00:15,044 --> 01:00:16,478
Shh.
[ Crying ] Bountiful.

1141
01:00:23,086 --> 01:00:25,721
How you feeling?

1142
01:00:25,788 --> 01:00:30,325
Stronger by the minute,
thank you.

1143
01:00:36,599 --> 01:00:39,301
Does this
look familiar?

1144
01:00:39,335 --> 01:00:43,405
Yes.
It surely does.

1145
01:00:51,614 --> 01:00:54,116
[ Birds chirping ]

1146
01:01:10,066 --> 01:01:12,868
Look at bountiful.

1147
01:01:12,902 --> 01:01:16,304
There's nothing left.

1148
01:01:43,599 --> 01:01:46,668
I'm home.

1149
01:01:46,736 --> 01:01:49,738
I'm home.

1150
01:01:49,806 --> 01:01:54,276
I'm home.
[ Breathing heavily ]

1151
01:01:54,343 --> 01:01:56,678
Thank you.
Thank you.

1152
01:01:56,713 --> 01:01:58,380
I'll pay you.

1153
01:01:58,414 --> 01:02:02,551
Ma'am, you better come over here
and sit down and rest awhile.

1154
01:02:02,585 --> 01:02:04,486
Yes, sir.
Don't want to overdo it.

1155
01:02:04,554 --> 01:02:07,856
Hope I've done the right thing
in bringing you here.

1156
01:02:07,924 --> 01:02:09,157
[ Chuckles ]

1157
01:02:09,225 --> 01:02:11,193
I don't see
what harm it can do

1158
01:02:11,260 --> 01:02:15,030
as long as you mind the doctor
and don't get overexcited.

1159
01:02:15,098 --> 01:02:17,833
Yes, sir.
Yeah.

1160
01:02:17,900 --> 01:02:21,069
I'll stay out here
until your son arrives.

1161
01:02:21,137 --> 01:02:23,872
Thank you.
You've been very kind.

1162
01:02:23,940 --> 01:02:25,574
[ Bird chirping ]

1163
01:02:26,809 --> 01:02:29,611
[ Groans ]
Whew.

1164
01:02:29,679 --> 01:02:33,482
What kind of bird
was that?

1165
01:02:33,549 --> 01:02:35,751
Oh, that's a --
that's an old red bird.

1166
01:02:35,785 --> 01:02:38,086
Oh, I thought
it was a red bird.

1167
01:02:38,154 --> 01:02:42,357
I mean, I haven't heard one
in so long, I couldn't be sure.

1168
01:02:42,391 --> 01:02:45,026
Do they still have scissortails
around here?

1169
01:02:45,061 --> 01:02:46,228
Yes, ma'am.

1170
01:02:46,262 --> 01:02:48,029
I see them out here
every now and then

1171
01:02:48,064 --> 01:02:50,031
when I'm driving
to the country.

1172
01:02:50,099 --> 01:02:52,634
Oh, I don't think
here's anything prettier

1173
01:02:52,668 --> 01:02:56,738
than a scissortail
flying around the sky.

1174
01:02:56,806 --> 01:03:01,510
You know, my father
was a good man in many ways.

1175
01:03:01,577 --> 01:03:04,946
A peculiar man,
but a good one.

1176
01:03:04,981 --> 01:03:08,683
One of the things
he couldn't stand

1177
01:03:08,718 --> 01:03:11,720
was to see a bird
shot on his land.

1178
01:03:11,788 --> 01:03:14,156
If the men
came hunting,

1179
01:03:14,190 --> 01:03:17,392
he would take a gun
and chase them away.

1180
01:03:17,426 --> 01:03:21,997
I think the birds knew
they couldn't be touched here.

1181
01:03:22,031 --> 01:03:25,267
Our land was always a home
to them.

1182
01:03:25,301 --> 01:03:31,673
Ducks and geese and finches
and bluejays and blue birds

1183
01:03:31,707 --> 01:03:36,878
and red birds and wild canaries
and black birds and mockers

1184
01:03:36,913 --> 01:03:39,314
and doves
and rice birds.

1185
01:03:39,348 --> 01:03:41,449
Rice birds get thicker
every year.

1186
01:03:41,484 --> 01:03:43,985
They seem to thrive out here
on the coast.

1187
01:03:44,020 --> 01:03:47,889
I guess a mockingbird
is my favorite of them all.

1188
01:03:47,924 --> 01:03:50,158
I think it's mine,
too.

1189
01:03:50,193 --> 01:03:52,027
I don't know,
though.

1190
01:03:52,061 --> 01:03:54,596
I'm mighty partial
to a scissortail.

1191
01:03:54,630 --> 01:03:55,897
[ Both laugh ]

1192
01:03:55,932 --> 01:03:58,867
I hope
I get to see one soon.

1193
01:03:58,901 --> 01:04:00,468
I hope you can.

1194
01:04:00,503 --> 01:04:06,474
My father
was born on this land.

1195
01:04:06,509 --> 01:04:08,076
And in this house.

1196
01:04:08,110 --> 01:04:10,111
Did you know
my father?

1197
01:04:10,179 --> 01:04:13,281
No, ma'am.
Not that I can remember.

1198
01:04:13,349 --> 01:04:14,950
Hmm.

1199
01:04:14,984 --> 01:04:19,421
Well, I guess there
are not very many around here

1200
01:04:19,488 --> 01:04:22,791
that remember my father.

1201
01:04:22,825 --> 01:04:25,760
I do,
of course.

1202
01:04:25,828 --> 01:04:27,229
My son.

1203
01:04:30,366 --> 01:04:33,101
Funny.

1204
01:04:33,135 --> 01:04:37,472
Ever since I've been here,
I've been half expecting

1205
01:04:37,506 --> 01:04:41,810
my mama and my papa
walk out the door

1206
01:04:41,878 --> 01:04:45,480
and greet me
and welcome me home.

1207
01:04:45,514 --> 01:04:51,786
When you've lived longer
than your house and your family,

1208
01:04:51,854 --> 01:04:55,557
you've lived too long.

1209
01:04:55,625 --> 01:04:57,359
Maybe it's just me.

1210
01:04:57,393 --> 01:05:01,796
Maybe the need to belong to
a house and a family and a town

1211
01:05:01,864 --> 01:05:06,001
is gone
from the rest of the world.

1212
01:05:06,068 --> 01:05:08,470
What's happened
to the farms?

1213
01:05:08,537 --> 01:05:12,841
For the last five Miles,
I've seen nothing but woods.

1214
01:05:12,875 --> 01:05:14,009
I know.

1215
01:05:14,043 --> 01:05:15,710
Land around bountiful
just played out.

1216
01:05:15,778 --> 01:05:18,513
People like you got discouraged
and moved away.

1217
01:05:18,581 --> 01:05:22,284
Yeah, but Callie Davis --
she kept her farm going.

1218
01:05:22,351 --> 01:05:23,485
Yeah, yeah,
she did.

1219
01:05:23,552 --> 01:05:25,086
She learned
how to treat her land right,

1220
01:05:25,154 --> 01:05:27,122
and it started paying off
for her toward the end.

1221
01:05:27,189 --> 01:05:30,659
Heard she was on her tractor
the day before she died.

1222
01:05:30,693 --> 01:05:34,996
Lonely death she had, all by
herself in that big, old house.

1223
01:05:35,064 --> 01:05:36,932
There are worse things.

1224
01:05:39,402 --> 01:05:40,702
[ Sighs ]

1225
01:05:40,736 --> 01:05:42,537
Well, looks to me like
you're gonna have a pretty day.

1226
01:05:42,571 --> 01:05:43,738
Oh, I hope so.

1227
01:05:43,773 --> 01:05:45,240
Are you feeling
more rested now?

1228
01:05:45,308 --> 01:05:47,275
Oh, yes, I am.
All right.

1229
01:05:47,310 --> 01:05:49,544
I'm just gonna head back
to the car.

1230
01:05:49,578 --> 01:05:51,179
You call me
if you need anything.

1231
01:05:51,213 --> 01:05:52,747
Thank you.

1232
01:05:52,815 --> 01:05:55,583
You'll never know
what this has meant to me.

1233
01:05:55,618 --> 01:05:58,019
[ Birds chirping ]

1234
01:07:10,026 --> 01:07:12,394
[ Laughs ]

1235
01:07:40,122 --> 01:07:42,957
Ludie: Mama!

1236
01:07:45,928 --> 01:07:48,563
Mama!

1237
01:07:50,132 --> 01:07:53,435
Mrs. watts: Hello, son.

1238
01:08:02,378 --> 01:08:05,613
[ Sighs ]
Hello, mama.

1239
01:08:07,316 --> 01:08:08,683
How do you feel?

1240
01:08:08,751 --> 01:08:11,052
I'm feeling much better,
ludie.

1241
01:08:11,120 --> 01:08:12,387
Yes, ma'am.

1242
01:08:12,455 --> 01:08:14,322
I got my wish.

1243
01:08:14,390 --> 01:08:16,224
Yes, ma'am.

1244
01:08:16,258 --> 01:08:19,260
Hope I didn't worry you
too much, ludie.

1245
01:08:19,328 --> 01:08:22,197
But I just felt I had to.
Yes, ma'am.

1246
01:08:22,231 --> 01:08:23,364
I understand,
mama.

1247
01:08:23,399 --> 01:08:24,933
But it's done now,
so...

1248
01:08:25,000 --> 01:08:26,734
[ Sighs ]
Let's forget about it.

1249
01:08:26,769 --> 01:08:28,837
All right,
Sonny.

1250
01:08:31,740 --> 01:08:34,509
You did bring jessie mae,
didn't you?

1251
01:08:34,577 --> 01:08:35,944
Yes, ma'am.

1252
01:08:36,011 --> 01:08:39,180
Well, now she's here
and she can get out the car

1253
01:08:39,215 --> 01:08:41,149
and come
take a look around.

1254
01:08:41,217 --> 01:08:43,184
No, she doesn't seem
to want to, mama.

1255
01:08:43,219 --> 01:08:45,320
You asked her?
[ Chuckling ] Yes, ma'am.

1256
01:08:47,590 --> 01:08:49,357
Did you ask
about your raise, son?

1257
01:08:49,391 --> 01:08:50,758
Yes, ma'am.

1258
01:08:50,793 --> 01:08:52,861
Mr. Douglas told me
he liked my work

1259
01:08:52,895 --> 01:08:55,230
and he'd be glad
to recommend a raise for me.

1260
01:08:55,264 --> 01:08:56,664
Oh.

1261
01:08:59,568 --> 01:09:02,604
The sky's so blue,
ludie.

1262
01:09:02,638 --> 01:09:06,241
You ever see
the sky so blue?

1263
01:09:06,275 --> 01:09:09,344
No, ma'am.

1264
01:09:13,349 --> 01:09:15,783
Callie Davis died.

1265
01:09:17,119 --> 01:09:19,454
Is that so?
When did that happen?

1266
01:09:19,488 --> 01:09:21,389
They don't
rightly know.

1267
01:09:21,423 --> 01:09:23,024
They found her dead.

1268
01:09:23,058 --> 01:09:25,393
She'd been riding her tractor
just the day before.

1269
01:09:25,427 --> 01:09:27,695
They buried her yesterday.

1270
01:09:30,866 --> 01:09:34,769
Mama, I should have made myself
bring you here before.

1271
01:09:37,206 --> 01:09:38,406
I'm sorry.

1272
01:09:38,440 --> 01:09:41,109
But I thought it'd be easier
for both of us

1273
01:09:41,143 --> 01:09:43,211
not to see
the house again.

1274
01:09:43,245 --> 01:09:45,914
I know, ludie,
but now you're here.

1275
01:09:45,948 --> 01:09:49,984
Don't you want to come inside
and take a look around a bit?

1276
01:09:50,019 --> 01:09:52,554
I don't think I'd better,
mama.

1277
01:09:52,621 --> 01:09:54,756
I don't see any use
in it.

1278
01:09:54,790 --> 01:09:57,759
I'd rather remember it
like it was.

1279
01:10:00,062 --> 01:10:01,563
[ Laughs ]

1280
01:10:01,630 --> 01:10:04,632
Old house has gotten
kind of rundown, hasn't it?

1281
01:10:04,667 --> 01:10:06,267
Yes, it has.

1282
01:10:06,302 --> 01:10:12,307
I don't think it'll last out
the next Gulf storm.

1283
01:10:12,341 --> 01:10:14,375
Doesn't look like
it would.

1284
01:10:17,379 --> 01:10:19,981
You know who you look like
standing there, ludie?

1285
01:10:20,015 --> 01:10:22,016
Who?

1286
01:10:22,084 --> 01:10:23,618
My papa.

1287
01:10:23,686 --> 01:10:25,019
Do I?

1288
01:10:25,087 --> 01:10:28,056
Just like him.

1289
01:10:28,123 --> 01:10:31,492
Course, I've been noticing
as you grow older

1290
01:10:31,560 --> 01:10:35,230
that you're looking more
and more like him.

1291
01:10:35,264 --> 01:10:38,633
My papa
was a good-looking man, ludie.

1292
01:10:38,701 --> 01:10:39,767
Was he?

1293
01:10:39,835 --> 01:10:42,103
You've seen his picture.

1294
01:10:42,171 --> 01:10:44,439
Didn't you think so?
I don't remember.

1295
01:10:44,506 --> 01:10:46,941
Been a long time
since I looked at his picture.

1296
01:10:47,009 --> 01:10:51,312
Well, he was always considered
a very nice-looking man.

1297
01:10:53,182 --> 01:10:55,617
Do you remember my papa
at all, son?

1298
01:10:55,684 --> 01:10:57,385
No, ma'am.
Not too well.

1299
01:10:57,419 --> 01:11:00,922
I was only 10
when he died, mama.

1300
01:11:02,825 --> 01:11:05,159
I remember
the day he died.

1301
01:11:05,227 --> 01:11:09,030
I heard about it as
I was coming home from school.

1302
01:11:09,098 --> 01:11:10,498
Lee Williams told me.

1303
01:11:10,532 --> 01:11:12,667
I thought he was joking.
I called him a liar.

1304
01:11:12,735 --> 01:11:14,402
I remember...

1305
01:11:14,470 --> 01:11:18,439
You taking me
into the parlor there

1306
01:11:18,507 --> 01:11:21,409
on the day of the funeral
so I could say goodbye to him.

1307
01:11:24,246 --> 01:11:29,884
I remember the coffin,
people sitting in the room,

1308
01:11:29,952 --> 01:11:32,120
old man Joe Williams
took me up on to his knee

1309
01:11:32,187 --> 01:11:35,590
and he told me
grandpapa was his best friend

1310
01:11:35,658 --> 01:11:39,861
and that his life was
a real example for me to follow.

1311
01:11:39,895 --> 01:11:44,299
I remember grandmama
sitting by the coffin crying.

1312
01:11:44,333 --> 01:11:48,636
She made me promise
that when I had a son of my own,

1313
01:11:48,671 --> 01:11:50,338
I'd name him
after grandpapa.

1314
01:11:50,406 --> 01:11:51,873
And I would have,
too.

1315
01:11:55,010 --> 01:11:56,944
I've never forgotten
that promise.

1316
01:11:56,979 --> 01:12:03,418
Well...
I didn't have a son.

1317
01:12:03,452 --> 01:12:06,654
Or a daughter.

1318
01:12:06,722 --> 01:12:08,456
Billy Davidson
told me

1319
01:12:08,490 --> 01:12:10,858
that his wife
is expecting their fourth child.

1320
01:12:10,926 --> 01:12:12,527
They have two girls
and a boy now,

1321
01:12:12,561 --> 01:12:15,363
and Billy Davidson -- he doesn't
make much more than I do.

1322
01:12:15,397 --> 01:12:17,265
And they certainly seem
to get along.

1323
01:12:17,299 --> 01:12:19,867
Own their own home
and have a car.

1324
01:12:19,902 --> 01:12:21,135
Does your heart good

1325
01:12:21,170 --> 01:12:22,870
to hear them tell about
how they all get along.

1326
01:12:22,905 --> 01:12:24,672
Everybody has their own job,
even the youngest child.

1327
01:12:24,707 --> 01:12:26,007
She's only 3.

1328
01:12:26,041 --> 01:12:29,477
She puts the napkins
around the table at meal time.

1329
01:12:29,511 --> 01:12:31,846
That's her job.

1330
01:12:31,880 --> 01:12:34,449
Billy said to me,
"ludie, I don't know

1331
01:12:34,483 --> 01:12:36,784
how I'd keep going
without my kids."

1332
01:12:36,819 --> 01:12:38,986
He said,
"I don't understand.

1333
01:12:39,021 --> 01:12:41,022
"What keeps you going,
ludie?

1334
01:12:41,056 --> 01:12:42,256
What you work for?"

1335
01:12:42,291 --> 01:12:48,529
I said, "well...
[Chuckles] Billy..."

1336
01:12:53,736 --> 01:12:55,937
[ Voice breaking ]
Oh, mama...

1337
01:12:58,507 --> 01:13:03,111
I haven't made any kind of life
for you -- either one of you.

1338
01:13:03,145 --> 01:13:05,913
And I try so hard.
I try so hard.

1339
01:13:05,948 --> 01:13:08,950
Mama,
I lied to you.

1340
01:13:08,984 --> 01:13:10,118
I do remember.

1341
01:13:10,152 --> 01:13:12,587
I remember so much.
[ Sighs ]

1342
01:13:12,654 --> 01:13:17,191
This house...
The life here.

1343
01:13:23,432 --> 01:13:26,701
The night you woke me up
and dressed me

1344
01:13:26,735 --> 01:13:30,671
and took me for a walk
and there was a full moon

1345
01:13:30,706 --> 01:13:35,510
and I was crying because I was
afraid and...You comforted me.

1346
01:13:35,577 --> 01:13:37,545
I want to stop remembering,
mama.

1347
01:13:39,348 --> 01:13:40,648
Doesn't do any good
to remember.

1348
01:13:40,716 --> 01:13:44,185
[ Car horn honks ]

1349
01:13:44,219 --> 01:13:46,587
We have to go now,
mama.

1350
01:13:46,655 --> 01:13:50,124
Jessie mae is nervous
I might lose my job.

1351
01:13:50,159 --> 01:13:54,462
Ludie,
what happened to us?

1352
01:13:54,530 --> 01:13:58,466
Why have we come
to this?

1353
01:13:58,500 --> 01:13:59,734
I don't know,
mama.

1354
01:13:59,802 --> 01:14:01,602
To have stayed
and fought the land

1355
01:14:01,670 --> 01:14:03,438
would have been better
than this.

1356
01:14:03,505 --> 01:14:04,906
Yes, ma'am.

1357
01:14:04,973 --> 01:14:08,276
Pretty soon,
it will all be gone.

1358
01:14:08,310 --> 01:14:10,711
10 years,
20 years.

1359
01:14:10,779 --> 01:14:13,047
This house,
me, you.

1360
01:14:13,081 --> 01:14:15,817
I know, mama.

1361
01:14:20,155 --> 01:14:23,324
But the river
will be here,

1362
01:14:23,392 --> 01:14:28,262
the fields, the woods,
the smells of the Gulf.

1363
01:14:28,330 --> 01:14:33,768
That's what I always
took my strength from, ludie.

1364
01:14:33,802 --> 01:14:37,705
Not from houses,
not from people.

1365
01:14:39,641 --> 01:14:42,410
It's so quiet here.

1366
01:14:44,079 --> 01:14:47,315
So eternally quiet.

1367
01:14:49,952 --> 01:14:54,155
I have forgotten the peace,
the quiet.

1368
01:14:57,593 --> 01:15:00,795
Ludie,
do you remember

1369
01:15:00,863 --> 01:15:08,135
how my papa always had that
field there planted with cotton?

1370
01:15:08,170 --> 01:15:09,637
Yes, ma'am.

1371
01:15:09,671 --> 01:15:13,207
See?
It's all woods now.

1372
01:15:15,077 --> 01:15:18,412
I expect someday,
people will come again

1373
01:15:18,447 --> 01:15:22,183
and cut down the trees
and plant the cotton

1374
01:15:22,217 --> 01:15:25,786
and maybe even
wear out the land again.

1375
01:15:25,821 --> 01:15:28,956
And then their children
will sell it

1376
01:15:28,991 --> 01:15:36,097
and go to the cities and
the trees will come up again.

1377
01:15:36,131 --> 01:15:37,932
I expect so,
mama.

1378
01:15:37,966 --> 01:15:40,401
We're part of all this,
ludie.

1379
01:15:40,435 --> 01:15:42,136
We left it.

1380
01:15:42,170 --> 01:15:47,675
But we can never lose
what it's given us.

1381
01:15:47,709 --> 01:15:51,679
Jessie mae: Ludie?

1382
01:15:51,713 --> 01:15:55,383
Ludie?

1383
01:15:55,417 --> 01:15:57,418
Ludie,
are you coming or not?

1384
01:15:57,452 --> 01:15:59,654
We were just starting,
jessie mae.

1385
01:15:59,721 --> 01:16:01,289
Hello,
jessie mae.

1386
01:16:01,323 --> 01:16:03,524
[ Sighs ]
I am not speaking to you.

1387
01:16:03,592 --> 01:16:06,327
I guess you're proud
of the time you gave us,

1388
01:16:06,361 --> 01:16:09,864
dragging us all the way out here
this time of the morning.

1389
01:16:09,898 --> 01:16:12,033
If ludie loses his job over
this, I hope you're satisfied.

1390
01:16:12,067 --> 01:16:13,701
I'm not gonna lose my job,
jessie mae.

1391
01:16:13,769 --> 01:16:15,202
Well, you could.
All right, jessie mae.

1392
01:16:15,270 --> 01:16:16,404
And she
should realize it.

1393
01:16:16,471 --> 01:16:17,972
She's selfish.
That's her trouble.

1394
01:16:18,006 --> 01:16:19,640
Just purely selfish.

1395
01:16:19,675 --> 01:16:22,076
Now, you tell your mama
what we discussed in the car.

1396
01:16:22,110 --> 01:16:24,879
No, we can talk about it
driving back to Houston.

1397
01:16:24,947 --> 01:16:26,614
I think we should have it out
right here.

1398
01:16:26,682 --> 01:16:28,316
I'd like everything understood
right now.

1399
01:16:28,350 --> 01:16:30,351
I got everything written down.
Do you want to read it?

1400
01:16:30,419 --> 01:16:32,386
You want me to read it to you,
mother watts?

1401
01:16:32,454 --> 01:16:33,588
What is it,
jessie mae?

1402
01:16:33,655 --> 01:16:35,489
It's a few rules
and regulations

1403
01:16:35,557 --> 01:16:38,025
that are necessary
for my peace of mind...

1404
01:16:38,060 --> 01:16:39,760
And I think to ludie's,
too.

1405
01:16:39,828 --> 01:16:42,096
First of all,
I'd like to ask you a question.

1406
01:16:42,164 --> 01:16:43,831
Yes, ma'am?

1407
01:16:43,899 --> 01:16:46,601
What possessed you
to run away?

1408
01:16:46,668 --> 01:16:49,303
Didn't you know you'd be caught
and have to back?

1409
01:16:49,371 --> 01:16:52,306
I had to come,
jessie mae.

1410
01:16:52,374 --> 01:16:54,709
20 years is a long time.

1411
01:16:54,743 --> 01:16:56,944
But what if you had died
from the excitement?

1412
01:16:56,979 --> 01:16:58,813
Didn't you know
you could have died?

1413
01:16:58,880 --> 01:16:59,947
I knew.

1414
01:17:00,015 --> 01:17:02,016
And you didn't care?

1415
01:17:03,885 --> 01:17:06,721
I had to come,
jessie mae.

1416
01:17:06,788 --> 01:17:08,089
[ Sighs ]

1417
01:17:08,156 --> 01:17:11,792
Well, I hope
it is out of your system now.

1418
01:17:11,860 --> 01:17:13,728
It is.
[ Sighs ]

1419
01:17:13,762 --> 01:17:17,865
I've had my trip,
and it's more than enough

1420
01:17:17,899 --> 01:17:21,936
to keep me happy
for the rest of my life.

1421
01:17:22,004 --> 01:17:24,405
Well,
glad to hear that.

1422
01:17:24,439 --> 01:17:26,941
That was the first thing
on my list.

1423
01:17:26,975 --> 01:17:29,910
Number one, there will be
no more running away.

1424
01:17:29,945 --> 01:17:32,179
There will be
no more running away.

1425
01:17:32,214 --> 01:17:33,848
Good.

1426
01:17:33,882 --> 01:17:36,484
Number two, no more hymn singing
when I'm in the apartment.

1427
01:17:36,518 --> 01:17:39,253
When I'm gone,
you can sing your lungs out.

1428
01:17:39,287 --> 01:17:40,454
Agreed?
Agreed.

1429
01:17:40,489 --> 01:17:41,722
Number three --

1430
01:17:41,757 --> 01:17:44,258
can't this wait
till we get home, jessie mae?

1431
01:17:44,326 --> 01:17:46,861
Honey, we agreed
I'm gonna handle this.

1432
01:17:46,928 --> 01:17:48,162
No more pouting.

1433
01:17:48,196 --> 01:17:50,598
When I ask a question,
I'd like an answer.

1434
01:17:50,666 --> 01:17:52,099
All right.

1435
01:17:52,134 --> 01:17:55,569
Number four, with the condition
that your heart is in,

1436
01:17:55,604 --> 01:18:00,374
I feel you should not run around
the apartment when you can walk.

1437
01:18:00,409 --> 01:18:02,143
All right, jessie mae.

1438
01:18:02,177 --> 01:18:03,344
Well,
that's all.

1439
01:18:03,378 --> 01:18:05,079
Is there anything
you want to say to me?

1440
01:18:05,113 --> 01:18:06,213
No, ma'am.

1441
01:18:06,248 --> 01:18:10,084
Well,
I might as well tell you

1442
01:18:10,118 --> 01:18:13,688
I'm not staying in that house
and watching over you anymore.

1443
01:18:13,722 --> 01:18:15,022
I'm joining
a bridge club.

1444
01:18:15,057 --> 01:18:17,024
I'm going to town
at least twice a week.

1445
01:18:17,059 --> 01:18:18,959
If you go now,
it'll just be a funeral.

1446
01:18:18,994 --> 01:18:20,294
You understand?

1447
01:18:20,328 --> 01:18:22,163
I understand.

1448
01:18:22,197 --> 01:18:23,564
Well,
all right.

1449
01:18:23,598 --> 01:18:27,334
Mama, we also agreed
that we can all try our best

1450
01:18:27,369 --> 01:18:29,070
to get along together.

1451
01:18:29,104 --> 01:18:30,771
Jessie mae also realizes

1452
01:18:30,806 --> 01:18:34,542
that sometimes she gets upset
when she shouldn't.

1453
01:18:34,576 --> 01:18:37,078
Don't you, jessie mae?
Mm-hmm.

1454
01:18:37,112 --> 01:18:40,014
Ludie: Let's start by trying
to have a pleasant ride home.

1455
01:18:40,048 --> 01:18:41,315
All righty.

1456
01:18:41,349 --> 01:18:43,451
[ Bird chirping ]

1457
01:18:43,485 --> 01:18:45,886
That's a red bird.

1458
01:18:45,954 --> 01:18:49,090
A what?
A red bird.

1459
01:18:49,124 --> 01:18:50,424
[ Sighs ]

1460
01:18:50,459 --> 01:18:52,560
That's what
I thought you said.

1461
01:18:52,594 --> 01:18:54,261
Come on.
Let's get going.

1462
01:18:54,296 --> 01:18:56,197
Do we go back
by way of Harrison?

1463
01:18:56,264 --> 01:18:57,531
Yeah.
Oh, good.

1464
01:18:57,566 --> 01:18:59,400
We can stop
at the drug store.

1465
01:18:59,434 --> 01:19:02,169
I am so thirsty,
I could drink 10 Coca-colas.

1466
01:19:05,607 --> 01:19:08,743
Are y'all ready?

1467
01:19:08,810 --> 01:19:11,011
Yes, ma'am.

1468
01:19:11,046 --> 01:19:12,947
Where's your purse?

1469
01:19:14,750 --> 01:19:17,284
Oh. I guess
I left it inside.

1470
01:19:17,352 --> 01:19:19,587
Where?
Oh, I'll go get it.

1471
01:19:19,654 --> 01:19:20,955
No, I want to go.
You'll take all day.

1472
01:19:21,022 --> 01:19:22,857
But you wait here.

1473
01:19:22,891 --> 01:19:24,525
I don't want to get left alone
in this ramshackley old house.

1474
01:19:24,559 --> 01:19:25,826
There's no telling
what's running around in there.

1475
01:19:25,894 --> 01:19:27,528
There's nothing around
in there.

1476
01:19:27,596 --> 01:19:29,864
Well, there might be some rats
or snakes or something.

1477
01:19:29,898 --> 01:19:31,432
I said
there's nothing in there.

1478
01:19:31,500 --> 01:19:32,767
Ludie: Mama.

1479
01:19:34,236 --> 01:19:36,437
All right,
ludie.

1480
01:19:36,505 --> 01:19:38,439
[ Bird chirping ]

1481
01:19:38,507 --> 01:19:43,043
Isn't that scissortail?
Look.

1482
01:19:43,111 --> 01:19:45,212
That's a scissortail.
I don't know.

1483
01:19:45,280 --> 01:19:47,314
I didn't get to see it
if it was.

1484
01:19:47,382 --> 01:19:48,682
They fly so fast.

1485
01:19:48,750 --> 01:19:51,619
[ Laughs ]
Here is your purse.

1486
01:19:51,686 --> 01:19:53,888
Now, where's the money
from that government check?

1487
01:19:53,955 --> 01:19:57,191
In the purse.
No, it isn't.

1488
01:19:57,259 --> 01:20:00,461
Well,
let me look.

1489
01:20:00,529 --> 01:20:03,330
[ Sighs ]

1490
01:20:03,398 --> 01:20:05,699
[ Laughs ]

1491
01:20:07,636 --> 01:20:10,204
